        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-09-18T17:22:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "you don\u0027t need intermediate Kind (\"Revision\"). Just make the ID of this ConfigGroup be\n   content_hash/index\nand then it\u0027s easier trivial to load.\n\nBut there is one thing to worry: when \u0026 how do we delete old entities from datastore?\n\nThe easiest way I can think of is to add `Version int` to the ProjectConfig. Every time new config (by hash(its content)) is fetched, then Version is incremented. Then, newly inserted ConfigGroup would store .Version at which it was created alongside a .CreatedTime.\nGarbage collection then deletes all ConfigGroups with *both*:\n  .Version + Y \u003c current ProjectConfig.Version   (keep at least Y latest configs)\n  .CreatedTime + X days \u003c now ago (keep config for at least X days)\n\nX is crucial s.t. new versions have time to propagate to respective RunManagers before old configs are deleted.\nI think Y\u003d5 and X\u003d30 would be good for debugging (for instance, logs are stored for 30 days).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 107,
        "startChar": 63,
        "endLine": 109,
        "endChar": 68
      },
      "revId": "77b2d17f0c6c635cc0af5e60302aacbb98c411ee",
