      "writtenOn": "2020-09-23T21:16:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Agree with `.Put()` them sequentially.\n\n\u003e copy pb.ConfigGroup by reference\n\nI\u0027m not sure how to do that given the type is pb.Config instead of *pb.Config (See my reply about why \u0027*\u0027 can\u0027t be added above). Shallow copy (`ret[i].Content \u003d *cg`) is not an option because go vet will fail with message \"literal copies lock value from *cg\" (I guess protobuf team discourage such usage). I think I may probably avoid creating new object by using reflection to assign pointer directly. WDYT?",
